151 1. JoHN ROBYNSON, citizen and broderer of Lon- don. To be buried in the “ Conventuall Church of Freer Minors in the Cite of London.'’ His body to be brought from his house “ atte Vyne '’ in Battersea, to the Parish Church there, and thence after dirige by water to Broken Wharf. “ I will that the iiij orders of freires in London and the preestes of Pappey doo receyve my body at Broken Warf and bring it to the conventuall church of freirs Minors aforsaid.'' Each Order and the priests were to have 65. 8d. for their labour. His executors were to provide 12 torches to be carried by 12 poor men from his house to the church, and thence to Broken Wharf and
